^B@2^*Bhondo717: ^*N|cp||at|That's true, he only had 5 hearts, but you didn't know that Shirley. Again, you can play what you like, but you will be missing a lot of opportunities to preempt the opponents if you have such rigid requirements.  Apparently, you won't preempt on many hands where you could. The idea behind a preempt is not to be precise. It is to disrupt the opponents.|
